<HEADLINE> Lao Acting Army Chief-of-Staff Visits Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Deputy Commander-in-Chief of the
Myanmar Defense Services and Commander-in-Chief of the Army
General Maung Aye met visiting acting Chief of General Staff of
the Department of the Lao People's Army Brigadier-General
Douangchai Phichith here today, state-run Radio Myanmar reported
this evening.
</P>
<P>
The meeting took place before Douangchai ended his six-day
visit to Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
Douangchai is the first high-ranking Lao military official
visiting the country since Myanmar Central Commander Major-General
Kyaw Than headed a delegation to Vientiane in June 1995.
</P>
<P>
At the invitation of Lieutenant-General Tin Oo, Myanmar Chief
of Bureau of Special Operations and Chief-of-Staff of the Army,
Douangchai arrived here last Wednesday.  
</P>
</TEXT>
