<HEADLINE> Ramos Reaffirms Commitment to Protect Children's Rights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, November 3 (Xinhua) -- President Fidel Ramos today
reiterated the Philippine government's commitment to protect
children's rights and welfare and ensure them a bright future.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with some orphans at the Presidential Palace, Ramos
said with the enactment of new laws, full protection of children's
rights and privileges will now be assured.
</P>
<P>
Ramos recently signed into law two bills approved by Congress.
One is about the establishment of children and family courts
throughout the country to enable kids who become victims of
neglect, abuse or exploitation to get speedy justice.
</P>
<P>
The other one is Children's Television Act which provides a
mechanism to monitor the contents of all television programs and
advertisements to create a healthy environment for the physical
and spiritual growth of children.
</P>
<P>
"There is not doubt that this new law will assure the access of
Filipino children to quality educational programs and, at the same
time, minimize obscenity and violence on television," Ramos said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the state shall act on behalf of children when
their parents or guardians fail or are unable to protect them, or
when they are victimized by their parents or guardians.
</P>
<P>
"Be assured that we will continue to protect your future
towards a more developed physical, emotional, intellectual and
spiritual welfare," Ramos said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the president also emphasized that family should be
the basic social unit that provides protection to children's
physical, moral, spiritual and intellectual growth and
development.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
