<HEADLINE> Special Orthopedic Clinic for Children Opens in Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, November 3 (Xinhua) -- A government-funded
orthopedic surgery clinic that offers free treatment for
congenitally handicapped children opened here this week.
</P>
<P>
The clinic, financed by the Health Ministry, will provide free
artificial limbs and other orthopedic equipment for congenitally
handicapped children.
</P>
<P>
In the clinic, set in a childrens' hospital, all congenitally
handicapped children with doctors' certificates can acquire free
orthopedic help including surgery, special shoes, metal stands and
wheelchairs. The equipment is especially made by Romanian doctors
and professionals.
</P>
<P>
Of every 1,000 Romanian babies, three suffer deformities in
limbs or other parts of the body, the Curierul newspaper said
today. In the past, parents of handicapped children had to pay the
orthopedic fees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
