<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Stock Exchange Gets Record of Turnover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, November 3 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwe Stock Exchange
(ZSE), the second largest stock market in Africa has posted a
turnover of more than five billion Zimbabwe Dollars (400 million
U.S.Dollars) between January and September this year, Chief
Executive Antony Barfoot said today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a finance students society seminar of the National
University of Science and Technology, Barfoot said the month of
July recorded the highest turnover of more than 700 million
Zimbabwe Dollars (56 million U.S.Dollars).
</P>
<P>
He said turnover this year has risen to more than five billion
Zimbabwe Dollars, four times more than the 1996 figure.
</P>
<P>
He said, ''With overseas markets a bit nervous, investors are
looking for new markets and we believe the ZSE will increase in
size because of new listings in future." " We need more listings
to satisfy all investors who are trying to invest in
zimbabwe,''he added.
</P>
<P>
He said: ''We have received a lot of enquiries from mining
companies especially from Canada. We believe that if that does
happen there will be a lot of job creation.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
