<HEADLINE> Thai PM Authorized to Pick Up Successor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, November 3 (Xinhua) -- The six coalition parties here
today authorized outgoing Prime Minister Chavalit Yongchaiyudh to
select his successor.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made during an emergency meeting of leaders of
the New Aspiration Party (NAP), the Chart Pattana (National
Development) Party (CPP), the Social Action Party, the Prachakorn
Thai (Thai Citizen) Party, the Seritham (Liberal Democratic)
Party, and the Muan Chon (Mass) Party.
</P>
<P>
The meeting also decided that the new coalition will still
consist of the six parties with the NAP as the core.
</P>
<P>
The coalition party leaders will meet on Tuesday to have
further discussions on the formation of the new government.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Chavalit earlier this evening announced that he
will resign soon and he has set to make a formal announcement of
resignation on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Chavalit made his announcement at a time when the Thai economy
remained in slowdown, in particular when the baht continued to
decline, plunging to a record low of more than 41 baht against the
US dollar.
</P>
<P>
Chavalit said that he had made his best to deal with country's
economic problems.  
</P>
</TEXT>
