<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Loses 12.42 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, November 3 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market today lost 12.42 points to
3790.82 as against the previous close of 3803.24.
</P>
<P>
The national index closed with a loss of 4.95 at 1639.21 as
against the previous close of 1644.16.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 closed lower at 369.17 from 371.39 previously.
</P>
<P>
Share prices fluctuated both ways on alternate bouts of buying
and selling and ended with moderate losses on the first trading
day after the holiday on BSE market today.
</P>
<P>
Brokers said that foreign institutional investors maintained a
low profile while investors in general had lost confidence and
made token deals being afraid to carry forward large positions.
</P>
</TEXT>
