<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Advised to Tap European Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's local food manufacturers
should take advantage of the European demand for imported Zimbabwean
products and increase their exports in that market, a German marketing
consultant said today.
</P>
<P>
Presenting a paper on food marketing at a seminar on productivity,
environment and trade, the German marketing consultant Gerhard Hiese
said there was vast potential for local food products in Europe.
</P>
<P>
He said European consumers had a high purchasing power which
enabled them to afford imported foods. He singled out France and
Germany as some of the countries with high spending consumers.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, if local manufacturers were to penetrate the lucrative
European market, they had to produce high quality products.
</P>
<P>
"Consumers in Europe are very particular about quality and
potential exporters should have a comprehensive understanding of the
market before they enter," he said.
</P>
<P>
Among some of the products that have a ready market in Europe are
poultry, frozen foods, fruits and vegetables, dairy products,
cereals, non-alcoholic beverages and fish.
</P>
<P>
Opening the two-day seminar, Confederation of Zimbabwe Industries
(CZI) President Jonee Blanchfield called on local manufacturers
to expand their markets by increasing exports to help the economy grow.
</P>
<P>
The seminar, organized by the CZI, will discuss consumer demands,
market requirements for food products and environmental cost
management in manufacturing.  
</P>
</TEXT>
