<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Africa to Participate in ACP-EU Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, November 3 (Xinhua) -- South African Deputy
President Thabo Mbeki will attend a summit of African, Caribbean
and Pacific (ACP) countries and their European Union (EU)
counterparts at a Lome Convention meeting in Gabon Thursday, his
office announced today.
</P>
<P>
It would be the first time that South Africa had participated
at this level in the renegotiation of the Lome Convention, the
office said.
</P>
<P>
South Africa's qualified access to the convention was agreed
to on April 24 this year, and approved by the South African
parliament on September 18.
</P>
<P>
The Lome Convention is an international agreement relating to
trade relations, commodity stabilization measures, and financial
and technical cooperation between its signatories.
</P>
<P>
South Africa has qualified membership of Lome. There are
certain advantages the country will derive from this: South
african firms and individuals will be eligible to tender for
projects undertaken in ACP countries.
</P>
<P>
Some South African commodities will also enjoy duty free
access into European markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
