<HEADLINE> ECOMOG Commanders Meet S. Leone Army Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Commanders of the west African
peacekeeping force (ECOMOG) have met Sierra Leone's chief of army
staff for the first time for amicable talks, military sources
said today.
</P>
<P>
The talks, held on Sunday in Orogoo, 17 km from the Sierra
Leonean capital of Freetown, focused on the modalities of a peace
accord signed last month to end the crisis in the country.
</P>
<P>
Buhari Musa who led the six-man ECOMOG team and Chief of Army
Staff Samuel Williams who headed the Sierra Leonean group had
friendly talks, said west African diplomats, quoted by a report
reaching here.
</P>
<P>
According to the peace agreement, signed in Conakry, capital
of neighboring Guinea, the military junta in Freetown, which
seized power in the May 25 coup, should hand over power to ousted
President Ahmed Tejan Kabbah in April next year.
</P>
<P>
Since the coup, forces loyal to the junta have been in a
virtual state of war with ECOMOG, which has been mandated to
enforce economic sanctions and embargo on the junta in a bid to
restore Kabbah.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, ECOMOG said they would stop disarming Sierra
Leonean soldiers passing through its checkpoints while the Sierra
Leoneans said they would return weapons captured from two ECOMOG
bases, according to military sources.
</P>
<P>
The friendly atmosphere of the talks has won welcome from
diplomats.
</P>
<P>
One of them was quoted as saying that "if the trend continues,
the peace agreement would far excced the expectations of both
sides."
</P>
<P>
ECOMOG Force Commander Victor Malu, based in the Liberian
capital of Monrovia, is expected to visit Freetown shortly to
plan the deployment of ECOMOG troops in Sierra Leone, one
diplomat said.
</P>
<P>
"His talks will focus mainly on the strategic positions to be
occupied by the allied troops for the disarmament of combatants
and the supervision of the supply of relief items."
</P>
<P>
These positions will include the main ports and strategic
locations in the city and the interior, he added.
</P>
<P>
In another development, Sierra Leone's chief of Defense Staff
Sam Koroma on Sunday sent a message of solidarity to his Guinean
counterpart on the 28th anniversary of the defeat of a Portuguese
led mercenary invasion in 1969.
</P>
<P>
President Kabbah has been on exile in Guinea since the coup.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
