<HEADLINE> Hezbollah Announces New Recruiting Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Lebanese Hezbollah Secretary
General Sayyed Hasrallah today announced a more lenient
recruiting policy that will allow all those who wish to join the
resistance the right to do so.
</P>
<P>
Hasrallah said in a news conference today that every Lebanese
who wants to join the fighting against occupying Israeli troops
will be admitted as long as he meets two conditions - a normal
level mentally, psychologically and physically, and no
relationship or contact with their enemy Israelis.
</P>
<P>
He said the would-be fighters will be put into groups named as
Lebanese resistance squads against Israeli occupation and
Hezbollah will lead them and provide them every condition to
defeat Israelis.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the Shiite Muslim Party of God will bear all the
responsibilities for the families whose member is killed or
injured when he fights with Israelis, he said.
</P>
<P>
Under the current policy, a Hezbollah fighter can get a
minimum of 300 U.S. dollars a month plus benefits such as food for
their families.
</P>
<P>
If he is killed, his family will receive a house, medical
care, education and monthly pensions of at least 350 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Now, most Hezbollah fighters come from the country's south, a
region of few economic opportunities.
</P>
<P>
In the conference, Hasrallah also announced a cellular phone
number for further contacts, saying that is for the sake of
security and precision.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that some 4,000 Hezbollah fighters with a
total of 20,000 supports are fighting in an attempt to drive the
1,000 Israeli troops from south Lebanon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
