<HEADLINE> Turkish President Urges OIC Countries Working on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Suleyman
Demirel said today that member countries of the Organization of
the Islamic Conference (OIC) should seek more effective ways
to tap the existing potential for their welfare.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the meeting of the 13th Standing Committee for OIC
Economic and Commercial Cooperation in Istanbul, Demirel said
that OIC has achieved a considerable experience in the economic
and commercial cooperation, but it is not enough.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the existing position is not satisfactory
regarding the economic and commercial cooperation, saying, "the
trade volume among our countries constitutes only 10 percent of
our general trade. We should increase this average to at least 30
percent."
</P>
<P>
He said that ethnic nationalism, racism, intolerance,
terrorism, organized crimes and some problems related to
under-development has unfortunately affected the Islamic world in
a large scale. But "By solidarity, we can solve these problems
which constitute obstacles in front of a better and fair world, "
he added.
</P>
<P>
The meeting of the 13th Standing Committee for OIC Economic
and Commercial Cooperation will end on Tuesday. 
