<HEADLINE> European Shares up on Wall Street, Hong Kong Recovery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Leading stock markets in Europe
all made solid gains and ended sharply higher Monday, boosted by
Hong Kong's recovery and a firm opening on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE 100 index on the London market reclaimed the 4,900
level and ended 64.1 points higher at 4,906.4, thanks to stable
Asian markets and a rally in New York.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that strong futures supported the market, while
gilts retreated as investors moved back into equities. HSBC led the
index higher on the back of Hong Kong's 5.9 percent bounce
overnight.
</P>
<P>
Guinness and GrandMet also rallied on news of their planned
capital repayment of 70 pence per share to investors.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, German shares closed the session up 127.38 points
at 3,854.07, with sentiment boosted by a stronger dollar and gains
on Wall Street Friday and Hong Kong today.
</P>
<P>
The market was led by VW's rally which was boosted by its
healthy nine-month profits.
</P>
<P>
French shares also closed higher in response to Asian gains
last night and a strong Dow, with the CAC-40 index ending at
2,787.96 points, up 48.66 points.  
</P>
