<HEADLINE> Welcome Ceremony to Be Held for Return of Axum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Addis Ababa business
community has raised near 290,000 U.S.Dollars for the the return
of the Axum Obelisk now in Rome.
</P>
<P>
According to a report here today, in a prelude fund raising
party held here Sunday, chairperson of the self initiated
business community Roberto Iacona said that coming back to its
homeland the Axum Obelisk deserves a warm welcoming ceremony as
its return is a joy and pride not only for Ethiopians, but also
for Africans and the world at large.
</P>
<P>
Present on the occasion, renowned businessman Sheikh Mohammed
al-Amoundi donated more than 1 million Birr (145,000 U.S.Dollars)
for the purpose.
</P>
<P>
Another donation was made by Fitawrari Amede Lemma,
parliamentary member during the reign of Emperor Haile Selassie,
who offered his parliamentary cloak for auction. The cloak
generated 36,700 U.S.Dollars in auction.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the occasion, Minister of Inforamtion and Culture
Woldemichael Chemu said the self initiated moral, financial and
material support extended by the business community is remarkable
in that it would encourage the activity of the return of Axum
Obelisk.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopian Deputy Prime Minister and Minister of Defence Tefera
Waluwa, Minister of Foreign Affairs Seyoum Mesfin attended the
fund-raising ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The Axum Obelisk was looted by Italian aggressors in 1937 and
it will be returned to its homeland in April, 1998. 
</P>
