order to make progress."
</P>
<P>
But Abbas made no comment.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli-Palestinian peace talks have been at a virtual
standstill since March when the Israeli government decided to
build Jewish housing units in East Jerusalem where usually live
Arabs.
</P>
<P>
The United States said this week's talks have a four-point
agenda: Israeli-Palestinian security cooperation, further
withdrawal of Israeli troops from the West Bank, a possible
"time-out" on Jewish settlements, and ways of moving to
negotiations on the final status of Palestinian areas. 
