<HEADLINE> World Cup Finals to Start Late </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, November 4 (Xinhua) -- The French Organising Committee
announced here on Tuesday that the 1998 World Cup final on July 12
will kick-off at 9pm.
</P>
<P>
The opening game on June 10 will kick-off at 5:30pm while all
10 World Cup stadia but Bordeaux will have at least one evening
match, for reasons of TV camera angles in the setting sun. Each
stadium will also have one early afternoon match.
</P>
<P>
First round matches will kick-off at 2:30pm, 4pm, 5:30pm and
9pm. Second round and quarter-final matches will start at either
4:30pm or 9pm. The semi-finals and final will start at 9pm.
</P>
<P>
However, the International Football Federation (FIFA) may make
adjustments to optimise TV audiences in other time zones.
</P>
<P>
Definitive kick-off times for the 48 first-round matches will
only be announced at the World Cup draw at Marseille on December 4.
</P>
<P>
The late starts contrast with USA 94 where many of the matches
kicked off at mid-day. 
</P>
