<HEADLINE> Hundred Flowers Movie Award Winners Announced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, November 4 (Xinhua) -- A list of the best films, the
best actor and the best actress of the 20th Hundred Flowers Movie
Awards of China has been published at Guangzhou, capital of
southern China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The three movies winning the best film award were "The Red
River Valley," "The Great Turn" and "Days Without Lei Feng," all
blockbusters earning high box-office revenues across China.
</P>
<P>
Gao Ming won the best actor award for playing a model Communist
Party official working in Tibet who died at his post in the film
"Kong Fansen."
</P>
<P>
The best actress award was given to Ning Jing, who acted as a
Tibetan girl in "The Red River Valley," which tells of the
struggles waged by Tibetan people against British invaders in the
early 20th century.
</P>
<P>
"Days Without Lei Feng," about a model soldier in the 1960s who
is well-known among the Chinese for his selfless deeds, attracted
nearly 500,000 viewers in Beijing in 10 days after its premiere in
early March.
</P>
<P>
The Hundred Flowers Award was established by the widely
circulated "Popular Cinema" magazine, with the winners chosen by
the magazine's readers.
</P>
<P>
The winners were announced Tuesday, as well as the news that
the Sixth Golden Rooster and Hundred Flowers Film Festival is to
be held at Foshan City, Guangdong, on Dec. 12-16.
</P>
<P>
The annual film festival is considered the most influential in
China's film industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
