</P>
<P>
The consumer price index slightly grew by 0.5 percent in
October to 107.9, on a base of 100 in November 1996.
</P>
<P>
Botswana's foreign reserves stood at 20.7 billion Pula (5.7
billion U.S. dollars) at the end of July, up 52.7 percent over 12
months, SAPA quoted the Bank of Botswana as saying. 
