<HEADLINE> Japan Grants Angola 18,000 Tons of Rice </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, November 4 (Xinhua) -- The Japanese government has
decided to grant Angola 18,000 tons of rice, and the ceremony
will be held here on November 11.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by a U.N. coordination agency for
humanitarian aid in a communique.
</P>
<P>
According to the communique, the aid is made to Angola under
an agreement for bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
A portion of the rice will be used to aid war refugees in the
country, while the rest will be sold and the money be used in
humanitarian projects in Angola.
</P>
<P>
This is the second time that Japan offered Angola food aid,
the first being in August of last year when the Japanese
government granted Angola 8,000 tons of rice, which were worth
about four million U.S. dollars. 
</P>
