<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong to Host World Squash Doubles Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 4 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong is to host the
inaugural World Squash Doubles Championships from December 10-14
at the Hong Kong Football Club.
</P>
<P>
The five-day event will draw 34 pairs from 14 countries and
regions into three championship categories: the men's, women's and
mixed doubles.
</P>
<P>
Among the participants would be the leading squash nations
Pakistan, Australia, Britain and Canada, with the world's best
players such as Jahagir Khan, current world champions Sarah
Fitzgerald, Chris Walker and Cassie Jackman.
</P>
<P>
Once the seedings are finalized in mid November by the World
Squash Federation, the 12 teams enterd in both the men's and
women's doubles will go into two pools of six. The top two of the
each pool will go for a crossover semi-finals while the mixed
doubles format will be a straight knockout.
</P>
<P>
The event will be staged on the doubles courts at the Hong Kong
Football Club, and the finals will be held on the portable
clearview court that will be widened to meet the world doubles
standard regulations, according to the organizers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
