<HEADLINE> Six Cities Cited For Environmental Achievements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 4 (Xinhua) -- Six port cities were commended
today for their outstanding achievements in coordinating rapid
economic growth and environmental improvements.
</P>
<P>
The cities -- Zhangjiagang, Dalian, Shenzhen, Xiamen, Weihai
and Zhuhai -- were among the first group chosen for the "Model
City in Environmental Protection" award.
</P>
<P>
The award is the country's highest honor in the environmental
field. The cities receiving this recognition must have a clean
environment while fomenting rapid social and economic growth.
</P>
<P>
State Councillor Song Jian said at today's ceremony that
achieving sustainable development in the urban areas is an
important goal in China's pollution control work.
</P>
<P>
Chinese cities have proved that they can coordinate economic
growth with environmental improvement, he said.
</P>
<P>
Wang Bingqian, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress, asked all the cities to take the six
cities as examples and increase efforts in pollution control.
</P>
<P>
China's urbanization process has speeded up during the past
decade. By the end of last year, it had 666 cities with a
population of 350 million. Heavy population, concentrated industry
and poor infrastructure have been an added burden on urban
pollution-control work.
</P>
<P>
With the Chinese government's unremitting efforts, however,
Chinese cities have made remarkable environmental improvement,
Wang said. Inspections have demonstrated that the environmental
quality of the six model cities is quite good even compared to
sustainable-development cities in the world.  
</P>
</TEXT>
