<HEADLINE> China to Speed Up Urbanization Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 4 (Xinhua) -- More than 10 million Chinese
will move to cities every year for the next 15 years, predicted
experts attending an international symposium on "Cities Toward the
21st Century", which opened here today.
</P>
<P>
These experts say that China's urbanization rate will increase
one percent each year in that 15-year period.
</P>
<P>
China has more than 660 cities and 17,000 towns. Its
unbanization rate has exceeded 30 percent.
</P>
<P>
Wu Liangyong, a professor from Qinghua University, said that
China's urbanization will speed up with its rapid economic
growth. The role of urban planning in the process must be
stressed, or nature and the culture will inevitably suffer, he
said.
</P>
<P>
More than 150 experts from more than 10 countries including the
United States and Germany will discuss sustainable urban
development, finance, urban planning and land use at the three-day
symposium.  
</P>
</TEXT>
