<HEADLINE> US Arms Inspectors Barred from Entering Iraqi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, November 4 (Xinhua) -- Iraq barred the U.S. members
of the U.N. Special Commission (UNSCOM) in charge of disarmament
of Iraq's arms program from entering three Iraqi sites for a
second day today.
</P>
<P>
According to U.N. sources in Baghdad, the Iraqi authorities
informed heads of three U.N. arms inspection teams that American
inspectors wouldn't be admitted into Iraqi sites, but other
inspectors could enter those sites.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the three U.N. teams refused to get into
the Iraqi sites without their U.S. colleagues, and that the three
teams returned to their base in Baghdad.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi authorities Monday barred two U.S. arms inspectors
from getting into some Iraqi sites that the UNSCOM was going to
inspect.
</P>
<P>
The move came as U.N. negotiators rushed to Iraq in an attempt
to diffuse the crisis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
