<HEADLINE> London Futures Exchange Trades Record in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 4 (Xinhua) -- The London International
Financial Futures and Options Exchange (LIFFE) saw its busiest
October ever, trading a record of 25.72 million contracts.
</P>
<P>
Statistics released today show that average daily volume
amounted to 1.1 million contracts, representing a daily nominal
turnover of 254.45 billion pounds (414.75 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
LIFFE, the largest futures and options exchange in Europe,
traded a total of 181.76 million contracts in the past 10 months,
29 percent up on the same period of last year and exceeding the
Exchange's total annual volume for 1996.
</P>
<P>
Jack Wigglesworth, chairman of LIFFE, attributed the record
volume in October to uncertainty surrounding Britain's
participation in Economic and Monetary Union and the turmoil in
global stock markets over the last week.
</P>
<P>
"The Exchange's record volume demonstrates the ability of LIFFE
to meet the needs of the world's financial community by offering a
wide range of instruments enabling market users to manage their
exposure to financial risk and volatility," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
