<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Herbs Can Prolong Life for Cancer Patients </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese traditional medicine,
integrated with chemotherapy, can help prolong cancer patients'
lives, a medical expert said today.
</P>
<P>
"Some herbs have proved to be effective for those, who are
suffering from cancer in an advanced stage and who are recovering
from tumor-removal operations," said Piao Bingkui, vice-president
of the Anti-Cancer Association of China.
</P>
<P>
Piao, who also heads Beijing Guang'anmen Hospital, said the
herbs can improve the immune system to help cancer patients
recover more rapidly from chemotherapies and surgery.
</P>
<P>
Clinical studies show that using Chinese oral preparations
together with chemotherapy on stomach cancer patients reduces side
effects and enhances the treatment's effectiveness, Piao said.
</P>
<P>
About 79 percent of the 103 advanced cases of stomach cancer
who received combined therapies survived more than three
years. And 55 percent survived more than five years. Both survival
rates are much higher than in cases involving only chemotherapy,
he said.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the integration of traditional Chinese medicine
and Western medicine, the hospital experimented with other forms
of herbal treatments such as injecting herbal medicines into
stomach and brain tumors and using herbs externally to control the
growth of superficial tumors.
</P>
<P>
Studies of anti-cancer treatments with herbal medicine has
already entered the fields of cell and molecular biology, he said,
adding that its role in preventing and controlling cancer has
attracted the interest of experts around the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
