<DOCNO> XIE19971104.0118 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Africa to Get Tough on Violent Crimes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, November 4 (Xinhua) -- South Africa is expected
to introduce amendments to its criminal law to get tough on
violent crimes, the Citizen newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
South African parliament will be asked Thursday to endorse
drastic new steps against crime, including automatic life
imprisonment for slaying a police officer, repeated or violent
rape, and robbery in which a victim is killed, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Under the Criminal Law Amendment Bill, gang-raping, repeated
rape of the same victim by one person and serial rape will also
carry a sentence of life imprisonment.
</P>
<P>
The new measures also provide a minimum of 15-year jail term
for hijacking and five-year imprisonment for a first offender
committing any crime that involves the use of a firearm.
</P>
<P>
Minimum sentences for crimes of violence, strict new bail laws
and laws enabling courts to sentence criminals to non-parole
periods of imprisonment are all due to be enforced before the end
of the year.
</P>
<P>
The bill was approved by the Justice Portfolio Committee of
the National Assembly at Monday night.
</P>
<P>
The bill proposed life imprisonment for any premeditated or
planned murder, which includes hit-squad cases, taxi and gang
slayings, as well as the killing of police officers or witnesses
in court cases.
</P>
<P>
Life imprisonment will also apply when a criminal kills
somebody while committing or attempting to commit robbery or
rape, or in cases where there is repeated rape, gang-raping or
serial rape.
</P>
<P>
A further clause provides life imprisonment for a person who
rapes a girl under 16 or a mentally ill woman, or who commits
rape "knowing that he has acquired AIDS or HIV."
</P>
<P>
Minimum sentences of 15 years for a first offense, with 20
years for a second and 25 years for a third offense, are set out
for another set of crimes.
</P>
<P>
These include any murder other than planned murder,
hijackings, robbery with aggravating circumstances, dealing or
smuggling in arms and ammunition, and dealing or smuggling drugs
valued at more than 50,000 Rand (10,400 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
However, in the case of gang or syndicate smuggling or dealing
drugs, the value of the goods is lowered to 10,000 Rand (2,080
dollars).
</P>
<P>
A third set of offenses carries a minimum of 10 years for a
first conviction, 15 years for a second and 20 years for a third.
</P>
<P>
These include any rape cases not listed in the more serious
categories, indecent assault on any child under 16 or assault
that causes grievous bodily harm. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
