<HEADLINE> Shandong Establishes Data Base on Provincial Conditions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, November 4 (Xinhua) -- Shandong, China's second most
populous province, is accelerating efforts to establish a data
base on the province's basic conditions.
</P>
<P>
First-phase compilation of the computerized data base, the
first one of its kind in China, has been completed and opened
to the public.
</P>
<P>
The overall project is scheduled for completion early next
century.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Shoufu, director of the Chronicles Office of Shandong,
said the goal of establishing the data base, which will include
400 million characters, is to provide policy-makers in the
province with economic, social and cultural information.
</P>
<P>
He said the province has been working on the data base for 16
years, with more than 10,000 archivists participating in the
compilation effort.
</P>
<P>
The data base covers the basic conditions in the political,
economic, natural resources and other areas, as well as the history
of social development.
</P>
<P>
The data base is divided into four specific coverage areas --
basic conditions, special subjects, statistics and supplementary
materials.  
</P>
</TEXT>
