<HEADLINE> s d s  1266 China-Three Gorges-Site Gigantic Red Flag to Add Festivity to Damming Process of Yangtze </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANDOUPING (Three Gorges), November 4 (Xinhua) -- A mammoth
five-star red flag, measured at some 1,080 sq m, is to add to the
festival mood at the damming ceremony on November 8.
</P>
<P>
The 40 m by 27 m red flag is to be spread over a slope-shaped
platform at the back of the reviewing stand.
</P>
<P>
"We designed the huge flag in order to celebrate the damming
process of the Yangtze River, since the Three Gorges Project is
the biggest project of its kind in the world," Xia Zhuhua, the
designer of the background of the review stand, told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
The gigantic flag is actually made up of woven rugs jointed up
by designers.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the huge red flag will be flanked by the design in
the shape of a sunflower, which are made up of 14,000 sets of
potted flowers and, there are also a profusion of booming flowers
and ornament plants round the buildings of departments and in
their compounds, and also along the roads.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the 76-m review platform will be surrounded by
various kinds of flowers and ornamental plants, and two flower
belts, 35 meters long and five meters wide, will be on either side
of the dignitaries and distinguished guests. 
