<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Premier Meets Spanish Visitor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 4 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng met with Josep
Pique, Spain's Minister of Industry and Energy, and his
delegation at the Great Hall of the People today.
</P>
<P>
Li welcomed Pique to China and said the relationship between
China and Spain has been going well since they established
diplomatic ties.
</P>
<P>
China highly appreciates the Spanish government's stand to
stick to the "one China" policy and not to have any official links
with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
He fondly recalled his 1992 visit to Spain and his meeting with
Spain's Prime Minister Jose Maria Aznar at last year's World Food
Summit in Rome.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have made substantial progress toward
friendship and a cooperative relationship not only in economic
matters, but also in politics and international affairs, Li
said. Their efforts also increased mutual understanding and
trust, he added.
</P>
<P>
He said China is willing to expand overall cooperation with
Spain, especially in the economic area. He said he hoped Spanish
entrepreneurs would communicate and cooperate with western and
central China.
</P>
<P>
Cooperation should not be limited to large projects only but
should extend to medium and small ones at which the Spanish excel,
he said. This would increase opportunities in China for Spanish
businesses, he added.
</P>
<P>
Pique praised China's achievements in political and economic
areas.
</P>
<P>
The Spanish people also cherish friendly feelings toward
Chinese, the minister said.
</P>
<P>
"The Spanish Government is ready to cooperate with China in
various industries," he said.
</P>
<P>
Spanish businesses sincerely want to cooperate with China, and
they are confident of building a good image in the Chinese market,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Also present at the meeting were Bao Xuding, China's Minister
of the Machine-Building Industry; Zhang Deguang, vice-foreign
minister; and Lu Congmin, deputy director of the Foreign Affairs
Office under the State Council.
</P>
<P>
The visit by Pique is by invitation of Bao. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
