<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Install Sewage Disposal Unit at Antarctic Station </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, November 4 (Xinhua) -- China's "Zhongshan" scientific
research station in Antarctica will get a sewage disposal unit to
solve its waste water problem.
</P>
<P>
The equipment will be sent to Antarctica with the 14th
Antarctic expedition on November 15, according to the State
Oceanography Administration's Third Research Institute in Xiamen,
Fujian Province. The institute is the producer of the equipment.
</P>
<P>
The waste water will be treated with artificially-bred
anaerobic organisms, that do not require oxygen to maintain life,
before being discharged into the sea.
</P>
<P>
These types of organisms do not exist easily in the South Pole
because of low temperatures, strong ultraviolet rays, and other
unfavorable factors, experts say.
</P>
<P>
"Zhongshan", China's first scientific research station at
Antarctica, was established in February, 1989.
</P>
<P>
A second station, "Changcheng (the Great Wall)", was
established in July, 1985.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
