<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People Who Map out World's Top Water Control Project (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANDOUPING (Three Gorges), November 4 (Xinhua) -- If
construction of the world's top hydropower station on the world's
third largest river -- the Yangtze -- is described as a play, then
the proprietor is the director, the contractors actors, and the
designer the playwright.
</P>
<P>
That is how engineers of the Yangtze River Water Conservation
Committee, who have been mapping out the blueprint for the gigantic
Three Gorges Project for decades, define their role.
</P>
<P>
Two people in the committee are often cited as the leading
brains behind the project. Zheng Shouren, its chief engineer who
stays all year round at the worksite directing construction work,
while Yuan Dafu, executive deputy chief of its design institute
who organizes the work of designing team on the back stage.
</P>
<P>
Zheng, in his 50s, has worked at the forefront of the project
for nearly four years, and what he and his fellow designers care
most is how to guarantee the damming of the river as scheduled.
</P>
<P>
"The main problems are the water depth at 60 meters and the
projected highest flow at about 20,000 cu m per second, both the
world's records," explains the chief engineer.
</P>
<P>
After months of consideration and experiments, Zheng and his
colleagues set forth a plan to dump rocks, boulders and gravels
directly from ships into the water in the gap between the two
sections of the cofferdam so as to guard against potential
collapse instead of the traditional method used in the past to
rolling them down from the slopes of the dike heads. When the two
sections jointed up, the river was then blocked by the cofferdam.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971104.0133 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People Who Map out World's Top Water Control Project (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The plan has effectively lessened the water depth at the gap to
about 22 meters and reduced the opening to 40 meters, which helps
guarantee the successful damming this Saturday.
</P>
<P>
When Zheng is busy at the dam site to implement design schemes,
Yuan Dafu also has a full schedule and is engrossed in the
formulating piles of design pictures, bidding letters, and working
on all sorts of technical reports for the Three Gorges Project.
</P>
<P>
Since 1995, the project has claimed almost all his working
hours, and the design institute's routine meetings had to be held
at weekends.
</P>
<P>
Known for his strict style of work, Yuan yet displays his
liveliness in spare time, which makes him popular among his
subordinates. Nevertheless, to his regret, nowadays he has little
time for his pastime -- listening to the Opera of Shaoxing popular
in his native Zhejiang province, and playing Chinese chess.
</P>
<P>
In spite of his packed schedule, Yuan, who is over sixty, keeps
the habit of jogging and practicing the traditional Chinese Qigong
each morning.
</P>
<P>
"A good health has helped me to be enthusiastic with every
piece of work," said Yuan, adding that it is all the more
important since nothing related to the Three Gorges Project is
negligible.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the work of designing, the Yangtze River Water
Conservation Committee also takes charge of plans for resettlement
and management supervision.
</P>
<P>
In modern civil engineering endeavors, management supervisors
are indispensable figures in control of construction quality.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971104.0134 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People Who Map Out World's Top Water Control Project (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the Three Gorges project, Yang Pusheng, chief of the
committee's management supervision arm, is the key figure to
ensure the quality of this largest scheme since the Great Wall
built over two millenia ago.
</P>
<P>
Yang noted that sometimes it was hard to avoid conflicts with
contractors in such a massive engineering scheme, and "when such
conflicts arise, persistence in quality is the foremost
responsibility of management supervisors."
</P>
<P>
On the evening of October 27, when supervisors at the worksite
found that the pace of construction at the cofferdams was a bit
too fast, they worried that might effect the solidity of the
cofferdams. Then, they urged the builders to slow down their pace
and, by midnight, the work finally suspended at the construction
site.
</P>
<P>
Since construction of the cofferdams upstream and downstream
was launched last September, according to Yang, supervisors issued
orders on workstoppage three times so as to ensure the quality of
construction.
</P>
<P>
A recent appraisal by the authoritative departments cited the
first-phase project as conforming with all the pre-set standards.
</P>
<P>
The words most often on the lips of those working in the
Yangtze River Water Conservation Committee are "we are a team".
And a long namelist can be found here to be related to the Three
Gorges project: Wen Fubo, one of the first designers; Chen Deji,
the main hero who located Sandouping as the site for the project;
and Cui Zhengquan, the survey master who found new homes for
relocated people...
</P>
<P>
"Turning the Three Gorges Project into reality fills us with
the greatest joy," said Zheng Shouren. "The credit goes to
generations of experts who have worked for the committee instead
of a just few people."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
