<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Ministry Spokesman Calls Jiang's U.S. Visit Big Success </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 4 (Xinhua) -- Foreign Ministry Spokesman Tang
Guoqiang told a press conference today that President Jiang
Zemin's visit to the U.S. marked the end of the twists and turns
in Sino-U.S. relations of the past few years and the beginning of
a new future. Tang also called the trip a big success.
</P>
<P>
In the first visit by a Chinese head of state in the past 12
years, Tang said the trip achieved the goals of improving
understanding, expanding common ground, increasing cooperation and
jointly creating the future.
</P>
<P>
He said the leaders of the two countries reached consensus on
bilateral relations, and specifically in forging a constructive
strategic partnership. "This is the most important result," Tang
said.
</P>
<P>
The two countries developed a framework for contacts between
high-ranking officials and multi-level exchanges, he said.
</P>
<P>
The two sides vowed to reinforce equal and mutually beneficial
economic and trade relations and to expand exchanges and
cooperation in environmental protection, energy, science and
technology, law, education and culture.
</P>
<P>
"The visit has also provided a sound framework and a solid
foundation for the cooperation between China and the United States
in maintaining world peace and stability, promoting global
economic growth and pushing forward economic cooperation in the
Asia-Pacific region," Tang said.
</P>
<P>
He said the U.S. reiterated its adherence to the "one-China"
policy and to the principles of the three communiques signed
between the two governments in properly handling the Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
"This is of positive significance to the proper handling of the
issue of Taiwan," he said.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also agreed to handle bilateral relations in
accordance with the principles of mutual respect, non-interference
in each other's internal affairs, equality and mutual benefit and
seeking common points while putting aside differences, in order to
properly resolving existing differences between them.
</P>
<P>
He said that President Jiang Zemin met with people from all
walks of life on his visit and contacted the U.S. Congress.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang's visit to the U.S. has brought
Sino-U.S. relations into a stage of historical development toward
healthy and stable development, Tang added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
