<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Showcases Latest Telecom, IT Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 4 (Xinhua) -- Asia CommuniTech '97,
incorporating Asia Networks '97, was kicked off here today for the
presentation of the latest products and ideas in the
communications technology industries.
</P>
<P>
It is the first exhibition focusing on international
telecommunications and information technology (IT) in Hong Kong in
recent years.
</P>
<P>
Organized by Hong Kong Exhibition Services Ltd. (HKES), the
show is being held at the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition
Center, in parallel with Asia Broadcast '97, which highlights Hong
Kong's prominent position in Asia's fast developing broadcasting
and film industries.
</P>
<P>
Some 14,000 visitors are anticipated for the four days of the
twin events, which combine exhibitions and conference programs,
said HKES General Manager Shaun Goh.
</P>
<P>
The HKES plans to establish the twin events as the only show in
Hong Kong and one of the major events in Asia which addresses the
issues of convergence between IT, telecommunications and
broadcast, he said.
</P>
<P>
Asia CommuniTech features goods and services from more than 150
companies which are taking advantage of the growing integration
between IT and communications technologies while nearly 100
companies are displaying their products at Asia Broadcast.
</P>
</TEXT>
