<HEADLINE> HK Launches Award for Effective Staff Communication </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 4 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's Labor Department
has launched an Award for Effective Staff Communication to
encourage, promote and benchmark the endeavors of establishments
in Hong Kong in achieving effective communication and harmonious
industrial relations.
</P>
<P>
Acting Chief Labor Officer Bertha Cheng said today that the
award is open to all non-governmental organizations in Hong Kong,
including small and medium-sized ones to participate.
</P>
<P>
"The assessment will be divided into three stages and be based
on four principles of effective staff communication," Cheng said.
</P>
<P>
The four principles are securing staff commitment, resolving
disputes, addressing grievance and welfare.
</P>
<P>
The panel of judges comprises experienced employer and employee
representatives and academics in the field of human resources
management, Cheng said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
