<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Marks Anniversary of Takeover of US Embassy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, November 4 (Xinhua) -- Tens of thousands of Iranians
gathered in front of the former U.S. embassy here this morning to
celebrate the takeover by the Iranian students in 1979.
</P>
<P>
Chanting slogans such as "Down with the U.S." and "Down with
Israel," demonstrators burned the flags of the U.S. and Israel,
showing their wrath against the anti-Iranian policies of United
States.
</P>
<P>
Holding placards with pictures of the Iranian leaders, the
mass shouted "Iran will not make any compromise with the U.S." and
"we will continue to resist the American arrogant policies."
</P>
<P>
Schools throughout the country marked anniversary of takeover
of the American embassy with the ringing of "Down with America
bell" at 08:00 hours (04:30 GMT) this morning.
</P>
<P>
In front of the former U.S. embassy, Iran's hardline
Parliament Speaker Ali Akbar Nateq-Nouri made a harsh statement in
the rally and called on the people to continue their
anti-U.S. fight.
</P>
<P>
He said that it was necessary for Iran's young generation to
understand the need for Iran to fight against the U.S. arrogant
policies.
</P>
<P>
On November 4, 1979, a group of university students calling
themselves students following the Line of Imam (Khomeini) took
over the U.S. embassy and held the embassy staff as hostages for
444 days. Diplomatic relations were severed in 1980.
</P>
<P>
The United States started an economic sanction in June,
1995, to punish Tehran for "sponsoring terrorism and seeking
nuclear weapons." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
