<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-President Meets with French Procurator-General </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 4 (Xinhua) -- Vice-President Rong Yiren has
said that Sino-French relations have seen good development in
recent years, with increased political, economic, scientific,
technological and cultural exchanges.
</P>
<P>
Rong made the remarks while meeting with Jean-Francois
Burgelin, procurator-general of France, here today.
</P>
<P>
Rong noted that Burgelin's visit will promote co-operation
between the two countries' procuratorates and said that Burgelin
held good talks with Zhang Siqing, procurator-general of China's
Supreme People's Procuratorate.
</P>
<P>
China will continue to concentrate on economic development and
the implementation of the reform and opening-up policy and
reinforce its building of democracy and a legal system in
accordance with the country's conditions, Rong said.
</P>
<P>
Burgelin said that the purpose of his China tour is expanding
co-operation with China's judiciary, and that the exchanges
between the two judiciaries have helped the growth of relations.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that the two judiciaries will increase
co-operation in the training of personnel and other areas.
</P>
<P>
Burgelin and his party are here as Zhang Siqing's guests.
</P>
</TEXT>
