<HEADLINE> Serema Williams Advances to Second Round </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 4 (Xinhua) -- Serena Williams of the
United States upset 27th-ranked Elena Likhovtseva from Russia 6-3,
7-5 on Monday night, advancing to the second round of the
Ameritech Cup women's tennis tournament in Chicago.
</P>
<P>
The 15-year-old Serena Williams, younger sister of U.S. Open
runner-up Venus Williams, will face fourth seed Iva Majoli on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In Monday's other first-round matches, Laurence Courtois
of Belgium beat Amelie Mauresmo of France 5-7, 7-6 (7-1), 6-4. Amy
Frazier defeated Jana Nejedly of the Czech Republic 6-3, 6-3 and
Nathalie Tauziat of France topped Ruxandra Dragomir of Romania
6-3, 5-7, 6-2. Joannette Kruger of South Africa also rallied to
beat Sweden's Asa Carlsson 5-7, 6-3, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion and top seed Jana Novotna, ranked second
in the world, drew a first-round bye in the week-long event.
Other top seeds include second seed Monica Seles, third seed
Lindsay Davenport and fifth seed Mary Pierce.  
</P>
</TEXT>
