<HEADLINE> Gold Price in Hong Kong Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 4 (Xinhua) -- The gold price in Hong Kong
today rose 2 HK dollars today to close at 2,889 HK dollars a tael,
according to Po Sang Bank, one of the major gold dealers in Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
The gold price is equivalent to 313.50 dollars a troy ounce, up
0.10 U.S. dollars from the previous close at today's exchange rate
of one U.S. dollar to 7.7355 HK dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
