<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Veteran Strikers Included in Japan World Cup Squad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, November 4 (Xinhua) -- Veteran forwards Masahi Nakayama
and Takuya Takagi have been added to the Japan squad ahead of a
vital home World Cup qualifier against Kazakhstan on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
First-choice Brazilian-born Wagner Lopes and Kazuyoshi Miura
are both suspended.
</P>
<P>
If Japan beat Kazakhstan they will snatch the second place in
Asian Zone Group B. That means they could play a two-leg playoff
against the runners-up of Group A for the third berth of Asia in
next year's finals.
</P>
<P>
Japan are currently second in Asian Zone Group B, a point ahead
of the United Arab Emirates. The final games will be played this
weekend with the UAE taking on South Korea at home on Sunday by
which time the Emirates will know if they can still qualify.
</P>
<P>
If the UAE lose against South Korea on Sunday Japan will
qualify for the play-off even if they fail to beat Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
South Korea had already qualified for the finals before
Saturday's match. 
</P>
</TEXT>
