<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets Five New Foreign Ambassadors to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng met
with five new foreign ambassadors to China on separate occasions
in the Great Hall of the People here today.
</P>
<P>
They are Chilean ambassador to China Octavio Errazuriz
Guilisasti, Brunei ambassador to China Pehin Dato Haji Mahdini,
Tunisian ambassador to China Mohamed Mongi Lahbib, Belgian
ambassador to China Johan Maricou and the Netherlands ambassador
to China Ate Oostra.
</P>
<P>
Li welcomed the five ambassadors to China, and wished them
success in their work and a happy life.
</P>
<P>
Li said to the Chilean ambassador that it is entirely possible
for China and Chile, both developing countries, to make constant
progress in political and economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He told the Brunei ambassador that China is willing to maintain
and develop a long-term friendship and cooperation with Brunei and
other countries of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations.
</P>
<P>
He told the Tunisian ambassador that China is willing to foster
an overall cooperation with North African countries.
</P>
<P>
He said to the Belgian and the Netherlands ambassadors that
China hopes to constantly increase the mutual understanding,
expand common ground and develop cooperation with Western European
countries while developing economic links with them.
</P>
<P>
The five ambassadors said that they are very glad to serve as
ambassadors to China, and are willing to do their best for
advancing the friendship and cooperation between China and their
respective countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
