<HEADLINE> HK Telecom Shows New Face in Regional Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 4 (Xinhua) -- Hongkong Telecom, Hong Kong's
only full-service telecommunications provider, shows people how
the convergence of telecommunications and information technologies
is rapidly changing the way people communicate at a regional
telecommunication exhibition here today.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, Asia CommuniTech 97, opened today at the
Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center. This is the first
major telecommunications exhibition in the Asia-Pacific region
ever held in Hong Kong. Hongkong Telecom's stand is one of the
biggest at the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
At the four-day exhibition, visitors to the stand can see and
experience for themselves how the telecom infrastructure built and
operated by Hongkong Telecom and the comprehensive services and
products provided by the company support their business as well as
personal communication needs.
</P>
<P>
The company aspires to provide the backbone for Hong Kong to
enter the "information age" and has been investing about four
billion HK dollars (512.82 million U.S. dollars) each year over
the past few years into its telecommunication network to equip it
with broad band capabilities.
</P>
<P>
Hongkong Telecom's Deputy Chief Executive Norman Yuen said:
"With broad band capabilities, our network will be able to support
interactive multimedia applications allowing voice, data and video
communications to be carried via the telephone line."
</P>
<P>
Seamless access to the Internet and business specific data
services, keeping in touch wherever one may be, and managing the
details of everyday living, such as shopping, banking, studying,
entertaining and engaging in real time interactive games, etc. can
all be done literally at the touch of a few buttons, he explained.
</P>
<P>
Visitors can see different telecommunications services and
products and telecommunication solution services at the
exhibition.
</P>
<P>
What Hongkong Telecom offers to the visitors includes
video-conferencing and view data services, super business
infrastructural service, Internet access services for both
businesses as well as individuals.
</P>
<P>
It also shows international communication services such as
satellite and mobile communications, caller number display service
and the screen phone, different types of collectible phone cards,
the fun-filled telecom world, the service pledges of the company,
and interactive television (iTV) services which will be introduced
very soon.
</P>
<P>
Visitors can take part in games which will help them understand
how the network operates, how telecommunications services help
their businesses.
</P>
<P>
They can also have their fortune link, and experience the
convenience of living in a digital home of the future.
</P>
<P>
"We hope visitors will go away after visiting our stand with
the knowledge of what Hongkong Telecom is capable of doing for
them and for Hong Kong as a whole and also the exciting changes
they can look forward to that will revolutionize communication,"
Yuen said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
