<HEADLINE> HK Newspapers Hail Jiang's US Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 4 (Xinhua) -- Major Hong Kong newspapers
today released editorials and commentaries to hail Chinese
President Jiang Zemin's visit to the United States.
</P>
<P>
An editorial of the Wen Wei Po said that Jiang's visit has
opened a smooth road for the development of the Sino-U.S.
relations of cooperation in the next century.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's visit to the U.S. is crowned with historic success and
the summit between Jiang and Bill Clinton marked an end to the
confrontation between the two countries and opened a new era for
Sino-U.S. cooperation, the editorial said.
</P>
<P>
The summit also promoted world peace and development and the
all-round cooperation between the two biggest countries in America
and Asia and created a favorable environment for China's
modernization drive, Wen Wei Po said.
</P>
<P>
A commentary in the Hong Kong Commercial Daily said that
Jiang's visit has achieved three major results.
</P>
<P>
First, leaders of China and the U.S. have reached consensus on
the prospects of the relations between the two countries and the
objectives for establishing a constructive strategic partnership
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Second, a mechanism and framework has been worked out for
strengthening the high level contact and cooperation in different
areas and at different levels between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
And third, the visit has promoted America's understanding of
and friendship for China.
</P>
<P>
Jiang wound up his nine-day state visit to the United States
Monday. The visit took him to seven U.S. cities.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Jiang held talks with U.S. President Bill
Clinton, met with U.S. congressmen and senior government
officials, and had extensive contacts with leaders of
U.S. business, commercial and other sectors.
</P>
<P>
This is the first official visit by a Chinese head of state to
the United States in 12 years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
