<HEADLINE> Chinese Party Leader Meets With Botswana Democratic Party Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 4 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, a member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party
of China (CPC) Central Committee, meeting today with a delegation
of the Botswana Democratic Party, led by its secretary-general
Daniel Kwelagobe, said the two parties and two nations have
maintained good co-operative ties and have supported each other in
national construction and international affairs.
</P>
<P>
"We thank the Botswana Democratic Party and the government, for
sticking to the 'one China' policy," Hu said. Kwelagobe's visit
will further increase mutual understanding and friendship and
contribute to bilateral long-term, stable and co-operative
relations, he added.
</P>
<P>
Kwelagobe said that Botswana and China have cherished a lasting
friendship and his nation and people will never forget the
selfless assistance and support the Chinese government and people
have rendered them.
</P>
<P>
Kwelagobe's last visit to China was 20 years ago. Tremendous
changes have taken place in China, he said, noting, "We should
draw from China's experiences."
</P>
<P>
He said he believes the 15th CPC National Congress will help
China to continue on the right course and score even greater
achievements.
</P>
<P>
Dai Bingguo, head of the International Department of the CPC
Central Committee, was present at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Kwelagobe arrived November 1. He is in China as a guest of the
CPC. After Beijing, the delegation will visit Hefei and Shanghai.
</P>
</TEXT>
