<HEADLINE> HK to Issue Souvenir Cover for Shanghai Stamp Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 4 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Post Office will
issue a prestige souvenir cover on November 12 to commemorate the
International Stamp and Coin Exposition to be held in Shanghai on
November 19-23.
</P>
<P>
The souvenir cover, at 2 HK dollars (0.25 U.S. dollars) each,
will be available at all post offices from November 12.
</P>
<P>
The exposition is jointly organized by the China National
Philatelic Corporation and China Gold Coin Incorporation.
</P>
<P>
It aims to promote Chinese culture and increase cultural
exchange between China and the rest of the world by building
up friendship among local as well as overseas stamp and coin
collectors.
</P>
<P>
It is also intended to popularize stamp and coin collecting and
develop the stamp and coin business in China.
</P>
<P>
On November 19, a hand-back service for special postmark and
cachet will be provided at all post offices to covers bearing an
indication of the event.  
</P>
</TEXT>
