<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-American Cooperation on Land Planning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 4 (Xinhua) -- China and the United States
have reached an agreement on long-term cooperation in land
planning.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was announced at the Sino-US Cooperation
Conference on Land Planning, which was closed here today.
</P>
<P>
The conference, the first of its kind held in China, was
sponsored by the American Planning Association and
the Land Administration of China.
</P>
<P>
The world's rapidly growing population and accelerated economic
development require more land and space. Therefore, the world is
facing the problem of maintaining a balance between the demand for
more land and the supply of limited land resources.
</P>
<P>
Some 100 officials and experts from both at home and abroad
attended the two-day conference and discussed various aspects of
land planning. The conferees reached a consensus on the importance
of rational land planning for ensuring the sustainable development
of land resources.
</P>
<P>
Jeffrey Soule, policy director for the American Planning
Association, said: "The conference has broadened our horizons on
how to better protect land resources." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
