<HEADLINE> Ugandan, Congolese Armies Launch Joint Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, November 4 (Xinhua) -- The armies of Uganda and the
Democratic Republic of Congo (DRP) launched a joint operation
last week against rebels, "The New Vision" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Over 30 rebels of the Allied Democratic Forces (ADF) have been
killed in the operation, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Security sources in Kasese District, western Uganda, said two
other rebels captured in Kyavinyonge area of Rwenzori Mountains
in eastern Congo had been sent to the army barracks in Bwera,
Kasese district.
</P>
<P>
Lt. Colonel Charles Angina, the operation coordinator in
western Uganda, held a closed-door meeting with top security
officers from the DRC in Bwera before the operation, according to
the paper.
</P>
<P>
Angina was quoted as saying that the Ugandan troops would
launch a joint offensive with their Congolese counterparts in
Rwenzori Mountains against the rebels, who use the mountains as
their bases.
</P>
<P>
Civilians in border town of Bwera in Kasese District confirmed
they heard shooting from Kyavinyonge last Thursday and Friday.
</P>
<P>
Rwenzori Mountains are area joining western Uganda and eastern
Congo.
</P>
<P>
ADF is a rebel group acting in western Uganda with some 350
fighters. Some of ADF rebels penetrated into eastern Congo and
keep harassing Uganda from their hideout in Congo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
