<HEADLINE> 3 More Suspected Coupists Arrested in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
lUSAKA, November 4 (Xinhua) -- Two Zambia army Majors and a
Captain were picked up at the weekend in the ongoing clampdown on
rebel soldiers linked to the October 28 foiled coup, Times of
Zambia reported today.
</P>
<P>
One Major was picked from Arakan barracks here together with a
Captain Musonda (only name given) while another Major was
arrested in Mansa in the north of the country.
</P>
<P>
The local newspaper quoted family sources as saying that Major
Berrington Mukoma whose family has since vacated their home in
the barracks was picked up at weekend.
</P>
<P>
Captain Musonda was also picked up from Arakan barracks,
according to sources.
</P>
<P>
Another Major was arrested in Mansa, who allegedly celebrated
after the announcement by Captain Stephen Lungu that the
government had been overthrown.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, some Zambia army Captains in Lusaka have gone
underground fearing the dragnet which has swooped many of their
colleagues.
</P>
<P>
Since the coup attempt was foiled just a few hours after it
broke out Tuesday, about 20 suspects have been picked up.
</P>
</TEXT>
