<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment in Tianjin Development Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, November 4 (Xinhua) -- The Tianjin Economic
Development Area (TEDA) in north China, has approved 2,900
foreign-funded firms, involving total contracted foreign
investments of 7.3 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The zone fulfilled annual targets by introducing 1.22 billion
US dollars in foreign investments during the first ten months of
this year.
</P>
<P>
Great Britain, the Republic of Korea, Japan and Hong Kong
account for some 66 percent of the total investments in the TEDA.
</P>
<P>
Total foreign investments in the real estate, transportation
and public infrastructure sectors stand at 790 million US dollars,
or more than half of total investments in the zone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
