<HEADLINE> S. African Commercial Aircraft Become Obsolete </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, November 4 (Xinhua) -- South African Airways
(SAA) is flying commercial aircraft that are up to 26 years old,
with all its Boeings over 12 years old, according to Public
Enterprises Minister Stella Sigcau.
</P>
<P>
In reply to questions in parliament on Monday, Sigcau said SAA
owned 43 aircraft -- 15 Airbuses and 28 Boeings -- by October 22,
and only its Airbus aircraft aged less than six years.
</P>
<P>
The 28 Boeings include five Boeing 737-200 aircraft that were
16 years old and eight that were 15 years.
</P>
<P>
Of the four types of Boeing 747 owned by SAA, only two Boeing
747-400 aircraft were six years old. All the rest were from six
to 26 years, she said. 
</P>
