<HEADLINE> International Container Port Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANTOU, November 4 (Xinhua) -- Construction of the Shantou
International Container Port, jointly funded by Hong Kong and
Shantou City, has been completed in the southern port city of
Shantou, one of China's major export centers.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the port, jointly funded by Shantou and a Hong
Kong-based international container shipping company belonging to
the Hutchison Whampoa Group, which is owned by Hong Kong
entrepreneur Li Ka Shing, commenced in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The port, which has an annual handling capacity of 500,000 TEU,
was completed at a cost of 90 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The port's two berths have a handling capacity of 25,000 tons
each
</P>
<P>
The port is expected to become the southern outlet for the
Beijing-Kowloon Railway, the nation's new north-south railway
artery. 
</P>
