<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Uses Lethal Injections to Execute Criminals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, November 4 (Xinhua) -- The Intermediate Court in
Kunming, capital of southwest China's Yunnan province, executed
four criminals today by using lethal injections.
</P>
<P>
The four died soon after receiving the injections and no
painful reactions was reported, according to a court source.
</P>
<P>
"Capital punishment can be carried out by shooting, lethal
injection, or other methods", according to the Article 212 of the
revised Chinese Criminal and Procedural Law, which took effect in
January, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The court began to study the use of lethal injections in
execution in May of 1996, a court spokesman said. More than 1,000
experiments had been done on animals by March 28 this year, when
the court executed criminals by using lethal injections for the
first time in China.
</P>
<P>
Of the 99 countries in the world that still have capital
punishments, only China and the United States use lethal
injections. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971104.0186 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East China Province Targets Expressway Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, November 4 (Xinhua) -- Officials in east China's
Shandong Province have set an ambitious target for road
construction to boost the province's economic development.
</P>
<P>
According to Zhu Zhengchang, director in the Transport
Department of Shandong, the province plans to complete an
expressway network with a total length of 1,590 km by the year
2000.
</P>
<P>
The expressway network will consist of three north-south
expressways, three east-west ones and a ring road, and it will
radiate from the provincial capital of Jinan.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the expressway network has alreay started. Two
expressways, the 91-km Jinan-Dezhou and the 85-km Jinan-Liaocheng,
have been completed and put into use recently.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said the two expressways will help strengthen the
province's ties with the Chinese capital and neighboring provinces
of Hebei and Shanxi.
</P>
<P>
The ring road around Jinan, which will stretch 118 km, is
currently under construction and will be completed at a cost of
4.9 billion yuan. The road is scheduled for traffic by October
1999.
</P>
<P>
Shandong now has expressways with a total length of 800 km, in
addition to 56,500-km highways. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
