<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Shares Close Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 4 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks fell over 4
percent to close the share trading today.
</P>
<P>
The key Hang Seng Index fell 474.33 points, or 4.21 percent, to
close at 10,780.78 this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Today's market turnover hit 25,210 million HK dollars (3,232
million U.S. dollars) compared with 23,704 million HK dollars
(3,039 million U.S. dollars) Monday.
</P>
<P>
The stocks rose 288.75 points, or 2.56 percent, to open at
11,543.86 this morning.
</P>
<P>
At the finish of the morning session, the stocks dropped 97.52
points to close at 11,157.59.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, the index jumped 631.33 points, or 5.9 percent, to
close at 11,255.11 as a result of a general stable outlook for
Hong Kong.  
</P>
