<HEADLINE> Chinese President Back in Beijing After US State Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
returned to Beijing by special plane this afternoon after the
successful completion of his state visit to the United States.
</P>
<P>
Those who greeted Jiang and his party at the Great Hall of the
People included Premier Li Peng, Chairman of the National People's
Congress Standing Committee Qiao Shi, Chairman of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference National Committee Li
Ruihuan, Vice-President Rong Yiren, Vice-Chairman of the Central
Military Commission Zhang Wannian, State Councillor and
Secretary-General of the State Council Luo Gan, Minister of
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation Wu Yi, Minister in charge
of the State Planning Commission Chen Jinhua, Deputy Director of
the General Office of the Chinese Communist Party Central
Committee Yang Dezhong, and Vice-Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's entourage -- his wife Wang Yeping, Vice-Premier and
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen and his wife Zhou Hanqiong, special
assistant Zeng Qinghong, Director of the State Council's Foreign
Affairs Office Liu Huaqiu, Vice-Minister of the State Planning
Commission Zeng Peiyan, special assistant Teng Wensheng,
Vice-Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation Sun
Zhenyu, Assistant Foreign Minister Yang Jiechi, Special assistant
You Xigui -- came back aboard the same plane.
</P>
<P>
William McCahill, charge d'affaires ad interim of the US
Embassy in China, also greeted Jiang at the Great Hall of the
People.
</P>
<P>
Upon completion of the visit, Jiang sent a message to the U.S.
President, expressing his "heartfelt thanks" to President Bill
Clinton and his wife, the government and people of the United
States for the warm and friendly reception.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said during his visit, he and President Clinton had
fruitful talks, held in-depth exchange of views and reached
agreement on the building of a constructive strategic partnership
oriented toward the 21st century between China and the Untied
States.
</P>
<P>
"We are convinced that the attainment of this goal not only
serves the fundamental interests of our two countries and two
peoples but also contributes to peace, stability and prosperity in
the Asia-Pacific region and the world at large," Jiang said in the
message.
</P>
<P>
"In the past few days, I have been personally touched by the
profound friendship of the American people towards the Chinese
people. Such a friendship serves as a powerful driving force for
the growth of China-U.S. relations," he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang called for China and the United States to "get along with
the trend of the times and work together to advance China-U.S.
friendly relations and cooperation and the lofty cause of world
peace and development."  
</P>
</TEXT>
