<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, November 4 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW -- The Russian Ministry of Energy would like to
cooperate with Japan in the development of fast neutron reactor
technology, ministry spokesman Kaurov said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement reached at a meeting in Krasnoyarsk between
Russian President Boris Yeltsin and Japanese Prime Minister
Ryutaro Hashimoto on November 1-2, Russia suggests that Japan
arrange funds for a BN-800 new motor unit for a neutron
reactor. In return, Russia would transfer its fast neutron
reaction technology, which has a good reputation for safety.
(Russia-Japan-Nuclear Technology)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BUCHAREST -- Romania and Croatia signed an agreement on
military cooperation here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the two countries will create a mixed
military council for close cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The pact was intended to enhance stability in the Balkan region
and to serve as a solution for the Bosnian issue, said Romania's
Chief of the General Staff Constantin Degeratu, who signed the
accord with Croatian First Deputy Minister of Defense Kresimir
Cosic. (Romania-Croatia-Military Agreement)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
