<HEADLINE> Northwest Chinese Company Looks for International Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, November 4 (Xinhua) -- The Xinjiang Production and
Construction Group, China's largest agricultural, industrial and
commercial complex, has recently opened a homepage on the Internet
that provides information about the group and chances to
co-operate with foreign companies.
</P>
<P>
The company, located in the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region,
has 100,000 ex-servicemen, some of whom transferred to civilian
work 43 years ago. It has seven million hectares of land, and this
year, expects a GDP of 15 billion yuan (about 2 billion US
dollars), said Zhu Jianfan, vice-president of the group.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the 1950s, the group began to offer agricultural
assistance to Vietnam. It has engaged in agricultural and water
conservation projects in Burundi, Afghanistan, Mongolia, Cuba,
Mexico, and other countries.
</P>
<P>
It was the region's first company to use World Bank loans and
foreign investment. By the end of last year, 70 foreign companies
had invested more than 160 million US dollars in the group.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said the group has 205 enterprises involved in foreign
trade, and this year's imports and exports are estimated at 220
million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
He also noted that the group will take advantage of China's
current preferential policy for western regions and will improve
the foreign investment environment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
