<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, November 4 (Xinhua) -- Fujian, one of the centers of
economic growth in China, is depending on four economic
development zones to build electronics development bases,
according to a senior provincial government official.
</P>
<P>
Liu Zhaocai, director in the province's electronics department,
says that Fujian plans to build electronics bases in Fuzhou,
Xiamen, Mawei, and Rongqiao, and expects an annual return of 45
billion yuan (5.4 billion U.S. dollars) from them by the year
2000. This will account for 90 percent of the province's total
electronics industry.
</P>
<P>
Fujian will have preferential policies for key enterprises and
projects in the Fuzhou Development Zone to support the computer
and telecommunications industries.
</P>
<P>
The Xiamen Development Zone is to be built into a hi-tech
electronics base focused on telecommunications, while the Mawei
Development Zone is being designed as a base for electric
appliances and personal computers, and Rongqiao as a computer
products base. 
