<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Farmers Rebuild homes Around Giant Reservoir Site </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sandouping (Three Gorges), November 4 (Xinhua) -- A new mode of
program oriented to comprehensive agricultural development are
helping to lead displaced local farmers in the Three Gorges
Reservoir area onto a road for better life.
</P>
<P>
The first group of some 24,000 peasant farmers, who used to
inhabit in areas which are to be submerged by the giant reservoir
under construction at the Three Gorges Project, have found their
new homes and been provided with the means of subsistence thanks
to the relocation programs.
</P>
<P>
These programs include the increase in farming productivity
in the resettled areas by transforming cropland with low and
relatively-low yields, building stable high-high yielding plots
and going all out to develop forestry, animal husbandry, sideline
occupation and fisheries, to accommodate the displaced farmers.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, new businesses have been established in the
displacement areas, providing additional jobs for some of the
displaced farmers.
</P>
<P>
The construction of Three Gorges Project, the largest water
conservation and hydropower generation project in China, which
started in 1993, is scheduled to be completed in the year 2009.
</P>
</TEXT>
