<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northwest China Reports Moderate Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, November 4 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Ningxia Hui
Autonomous Region, one of the leading grain producers in the
country, expects annual economic growth of 7.5 percent this year,
according to the local statistics bureau.
</P>
<P>
This year, the region has had record grain production with the
output reaching 2.56 million tons and improved development in
animal husbandry.
</P>
<P>
By the end of September, Ningxia had 924,000 head of livestock,
8.1 percent more than for last year. Meat output was 88,500 tons,
a 10.8 percent rise.
</P>
<P>
Township-run enterprises had 6.5 billion yuan in output in the
first three quarters of the year, 26.5 percent more than for that
period a year ago.
</P>
<P>
Industry grew 5.2 percent, with output value of 13.5 billion
yuan by the end of September. The growth rate of heavy industry
was higher than that of light industry.
</P>
<P>
Imports and exports came to 227 million through September, a
62-percent rise.
</P>
<P>
Retail sales were up 2.4 percent in the first three quarters,
4.2 percentage points lower than a year ago.  
</P>
</TEXT>
