<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Expects to Need over 200,000 Commercial Vehicles Annually </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 4 (Xinhua) -- China Business Times reports
that the nation's public transportation sector will need at least
200,000 new buses and taxicabs annually.
</P>
<P>
China's transportation fleet currently includes 160,000 public
buses and over 600,000 taxicabs. Li Shihao, deputy general manager
of the China National Urban Vehicle Corp., said the new vehicles
will simply replace older ones in the fleet.
</P>
<P>
An increasing number of people are opting to travel long
distances by bus, with an estimated 20,000 long-distance buses
needed on an annual basis, said Li.
</P>
<P>
China has over 50 commercial motor vehicle manufacturing plants
with a total annual output of over 50,000 units. The vast majority
of the plants are seeking foreign funding and technology to revamp
outdated facilities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
