<HEADLINE> Trade Zone to Benefit as Harbour Develops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 4 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Waigaoqiao Free
Trade Zone Development Co., Ltd. will benefit from the
construction of an adjacent container port.
</P>
<P>
The company, the sole developer of the zone, will take
advantage of the port's expansion to build warehouses on its newly
acquired land of 1.7 square kilometers for companies using the
port to lease, company chairman Ruan Yanhua said.
</P>
<P>
The company, which has listed both A and B shares on the
Shanghai Stock Exchange, plans an allotment within the year to
raise funds for developing the land, Ruan said.
</P>
<P>
The Waigaoqiao port is one of the seven container ports in
Shanghai and the port is expanding its handling capacity from the
current 500,000 tons per year to 1.4 million tons per year, which
prompted Ruan's company to use the opportunity to enlarge its
warehouse area.
</P>
<P>
With the new construction, the company's warehouse rents should
increase rapidly, Ruan said.
</P>
<P>
The Waigaoqiao Free Trade Zone, a major part of the formative
Pudong New Area, is China's first trade zone.
</P>
<P>
Its strong infrastructure facilities, including a deep water
port, electric power station and high-standard processing plants
and warehouses, have attracted some 3.7 billion U.S.dollars in
investment, including over 2.5 billion U.S.dollars from foreign
firms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
