<HEADLINE> Coca Cola to Make Huge Investment in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, November 4 (Xinhua) -- The world's leading soft drink
manufacturer Coca Cola company is planning to make
multi-million-U.S.-dollar new investment in Bangladesh to tap the
untapped opportunities in soft drink market and to demonstrate its
confidence in the country's economic prospects.
</P>
<P>
According to the company's Southeast and West Asia Division
President Andrew Angle, the Coca Cola products are leading the
market in Bangladesh with a 56 percent share of carbonated soft
drink sales. But per capita consumption of Coca Cola products in
the country is only two (bottles) compared with three times more
in neighboring India and Pakistan and 105 times more in the
Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Additional multi-million-dollar investment would be made for
the expansion of infrastructure and distribution system of the
company which had long-time presence in this South Asian country,
Angle said.
</P>
<P>
"Here in Bangladesh, a growing economy and rapidly changing
soft drink market offers numerous untapped opportunities," he
added.
</P>
<P>
The Coca Cola company started its operations in Bangladesh in
1962. There are now three production facilities, which are
respectively located in the capital Dhaka, the second largest city
of Chittagong, and Comilla. 
</P>
</TEXT>
