<HEADLINE> Gas, Oil Exploration in Bangladeshi Hilly Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, November 4 (Xinhua) -- The exploration of natural gas
and oil in Rangamati district 230 kilometers from Dhaka has begun,
and the exploration in two other demarcated areas 260 kilometers
from the capital will begin later this month, a local newspaper
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The United Meridian Corporation, an oil exploration company of
the U.S., started survey with the assistance of the security
forces, the Bangladesh Observer said.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. oil company signed an agreement with the Petrobangla
of Bangladesh last February to carry out oil and gas exploration
in the three hilly areas of Rangamati, Khagrachhair and
Bandarban, and Cox's Bazar, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
The company will invest 12.4 billion U.S. dollars in the
seven-year- long project, the newspaper said. It has also taken
the initiative to appoint 1,500 workers for the project.
</P>
<P>
The whole exploration work will be carried out in an area of
about 13,000 square kilometers in the three hilly districts and
Cox's Bazar, the newspaper added.  
</P>
