<HEADLINE> India's Foreign Reserves Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, November 4 (Xinhua) -- India's foreign exchange
reserves increased to surpass 30 billion U.S. dollars on October
24, official sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
Good U.S. dollar inflows and the Reserve Bank of India's (RBI)
timely intervention in the foreign exchange market enabled the
country's reserves to touch 30.012 billion and restored confidence
in the country's currency, which witnessed a sharp fall during the
second fortnight of August this year.
</P>
<P>
Strong inflows indicate that the rupee will remain strong and
the RBI will find it difficult to devalue the rupee as demanded by
the exporters in the country.  
</P>
