<HEADLINE> Hungary to Promote Sino-Hungarian Ties: Speaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Hungary is willing to promote
the Sino-Hungarian relations on the basis of equality and mutual
benefit, President of Hungarian National Assembly Gal Zoltan said
here today.
</P>
<P>
The Speaker made the remarks when meeting with Zhu Liang,
chairman of Foreign Affairs Committee of National People's
Congress (NPC) of China, who headed a NPC delegation paying a
visit to the Eastern European country.
</P>
<P>
Gal said that China is one of the powers which can play a
decisive role to the world's politics, and a stable China plays an
important role in maintaining the world's stability. He hoped that
China will continue to go along her own developing way in the
future.
</P>
<P>
Everything is ready for deepening the bilateral ties since
Hungarian delegations from various political parties visited China
recently, Gal said. He added that the Hungarians who have been to
China have learned to know that China is a big country with its
distinctive history and traditions.
</P>
<P>
Hungary and China should further increase the exchange of
friendly visits and get a deeper mutual understanding, Gal said,
hoping that the two parliaments should play a greater role in the
future cooperation between them.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting Zhu Liang reviewed the bilateral ties after
Gal visited China in last May and briefed the hosts about the
political and economic situation in China as well as China's
foreign policy. He believed that with joint efforts, both
countries will achieve a sound development of their economic
relations.
</P>
<P>
The NPC delegation, which arrived here on October 30, will
leave for Greece on Tuesday. 
