<DOCNO> XIE19971104.0242 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three Gorges Project:A Dream of the Chinese Nation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANDOUPING (Three Gorges), November 4 (Xinhua) -- The Yangtze
is to be blocked this Saturday, signaling the completion of the
first stage of the gigantic Three Gorges Project. The project has
been a dream long cherished by the Chinese nation almost for a
century.
</P>
<P>
In the 1910s, Dr. Sun Yat-sen, forerunner of the Chinese
democratic revolution, became the first to propose the
construction of a gigantic water control project around the Three
Gorges in the middle reaches of the Yangtze, China's largest
river.
</P>
<P>
A major flood occurred on the Yangtze once every decade during
the two millenia from the Han Dynasty (206 BC-AD 220) to the end
of the Qing Dynasty (1644-1911), and two catastrophic floods in the
thirties of this century alone claimed 300,000 lives along the
river.
</P>
<P>
Upon the founding of the People's Republic of China in 1949,
the first generation of New China's leaders headed by Mao Zedong
started to draw up a blueprint for the project.
</P>
<P>
After four decades of investigations, planning and debate,
the Three Gorges Project was finally approved by the National
People's Congress -- the Chinese parliament - in 1992.
</P>
<P>
As the world's top water control scheme, it is projected to
cost some 25 billion US dollars. The investment is estimated to
account for less than one thousandth of the cumulative GDP during
the 17 years of construction, thanks to enhanced national strength
in the wake of China's reform and opening-up policies adopted 18
years ago.
</P>
<P>
A series of knotty problems are involved in the project: the
amount of work of the project is the largest in the world, the
technologies to be used in the project are complex and the 1.2
million people to be relocated in the project area are
unprecedented.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the project has been focused on a market
mechanism and international conventional practices. After five
years of its initiation, the first stage of the project is
completed ahead of schedule, construction quality has complied
with the pre-designed standards, and the actual investment is four
billion yuan less than the initial projected budget.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, a development-oriented resettlement program has
helped the displaced farmers to become the first to be better-off
in the Three Gorges area. By now more than 60,000 farmers have
been resettled.
</P>
<P>
The Three Gorges Fund, a major source for the massive
investment in the project, is based on an appropriate price
increase in power charges across the country. From 1993-1997, the
fund collected a total of 13.7 billion yuan, equivalent to an
average of 11 yuan contributed by every Chinese.
</P>
<P>
The dream of the Three Gorges Project represent the Chinese
people's aspiration for building a stronger China.
</P>
<P>
Upon its completion in 12 years, the project will bring huge
benefit to the nation by putting an end to floods in the middle
and lower reaches of the Yangtze, relieving 15 million people of
the scourge of flood, and providing an average of additional 70 kw
of electricity for each Chinese every year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971104.0243 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chile's Industrial Sales Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Chile's domestic and foreign
sales of manufactured products enjoyed a 13.3 percent increase so
far this year, said the Industry Fostering Society today.
</P>
<P>
The boost, the society said, contributed to an accumulated rise
of 5.9 percent in total industrial sales.
</P>
<P>
The export surge in September fueled the country's
manufacturing sectors, especially those of fish meal, cellulose
and metal, which propped up 160 percent in value.
</P>
<P>
The home market grew by 7.6 percent in September, against the
same month of 1996; and by 4.1 percent in the first nine months of
the year, with respect to the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
While the manufacturing sectors' output soared 8 percent in
September, the Chile's overall industrial output gained 4.3
percent in the year's first nine months, the society said. 
</P>
