<HEADLINE> Shanghai Highways </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 4 (Xinhua) -- Transportation authorities
report that good management has ensured that Shanghai's highways
are smooth, clean and beautiful.
</P>
<P>
Experts from the Ministry of Communications offered the
appraisal following a three-day examination of local highways.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's highway construction and maintenance have been the
subject of steady and rapid development in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years alone, the city has invested 12
billion yuan (1.44 billion US dollars) to either build or improve
a number of high-grade roads, including the Shanghai section of
the Shanghai-Nanjing Expressway and the Pudong section of the
Inner Ring Road.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's highway system currently stretches a total of 3,880
kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Officials have also focused on improving highway maintenance
and beautifying the environment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
