<HEADLINE> Bio-Pharmaceutical Industry Booms in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 4 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's leading
industrial city, has witnessed the rapid growth of modern
biological pharmaceutical enterprises with profits of 130 million
yuan (15 million US dollars) earned last year.
</P>
<P>
The industrial output value of bio-pharmaceutical ventures
reached 12 billion yuan (3.6 billion dollars) in 1996, with 98
percent of products sold on the market.
</P>
<P>
The city has registered more than 50 pharmaceutical and
high-tech bio-pharmaceutical enterprises, including 45
Sino-foreign funded ventures.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investors include major transnational companies from
Germany, Switzerland and Norway.
</P>
<P>
The sector has emerged as a new pillar industry in the city,
and the municipal government has established a special office to
regulate related activities.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the city allocated 300 million yuan (36 million
dollars) for the scientific and technological development of
modern bio-pharmaceuticals. 
</P>
