<HEADLINE> NZ National Party to Have New Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, November 4 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand National
Party has confirmed that Minister of State-owned Enterprises Jenny
Shipley will take over as the new leader of the Party later this
month to replace Prime Minister Jim Bolger.
</P>
<P>
An announcement was made after a National caucus meeting this
morning. It means that NZ will have its first woman prime minister
at the end of the month after Bolger resigned from the prime
ministership.
</P>
<P>
However, Bolger will stay as prime minister until he returns
from the Vancouver APEC meeting and a trip to China.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference, Shipley said she has been given
the authority to work during that month on transitional coalition
arrangements.
</P>
<P>
"It is very important that New Zealand has certainty at this
time," she said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, New Zealand First, the junior partner in the
coalition, is having its caucus meeting behind doors this morning
to discuss the implication of the leadership change in the
government.
</P>
<P>
NZ First leader Winston Peters refused to make any comment as
he was heading to the meeting room.  
</P>
