<HEADLINE> Two Australian Winter Olympics Hopefuls Fail Drug Test </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, November 4 (Xinhua) -- Two hopefuls for Australia's
Winter Olympic team for Nagano Olympics have tested positive to
steroids, the Australian Olympic Committee (AOC) president John
Coates confirmed in Sydney on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The two bobsled competitors had tested positive to stanozolol,
the steroid used by Canadian sprinter Ben Johnson at the 1988
Olympics.
</P>
<P>
The tests were taken at an Olympic team assembly in Sydney in
September but Coates refused to identify the pair.
</P>
<P>
The pair would soon face a hearing before the National Sports
Dispute Resolution Center, and they would face two-year ban if
the hearing found against them.
</P>
<P>
An Australian bobsled team has yet to qualify for selection for
the Nagano Games in February at this weekend. 
</P>
