<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Poland's Economy Keeps Good Momentum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Poland's economy has maintained
a healthy growth momentum since the beginning of the year, the
statistics bureau of Poland said in a recent communique.
</P>
<P>
The communique said that during the first nine months,
industrial output increased by 11.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
During that time period, retail trade rose 14.6 percent. The
price index dropped by a wide margin compared to the same period
last year, according to the document.
</P>
<P>
During the first three quarters, the unemployment rate declined
to 10.6 percent from the same period a year ago.
</P>
<P>
The bureau said that an inflation rate of 15 percent, which was
predicted for this year, would probably be reached. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
