<DOCNO> XIE19971104.0277 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> d p s 1271 China-Three Gorges-Backgrounder-11 Backgrounder: Three Gorges Reservoir Inundation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANDOUPING (Three Gorges), November 4 (Xinhua) -- The Three
Gorges Reservoir will inundate 632 sq. km., the world's largest
inundated area by a single project.
</P>
<P>
The normal water level of 175 meters will be achieved in the
year 2003, with the reservoir covering 1,045 sq.km. and stretching
some 663 km, an area capable of controlling floods expected to
occur twice in one decade.
</P>
<P>
The resettlement effort and the area to be inundated are
unprecedented in Chinese history, with inundation affecting 365
townships in 21 counties, cities or districts in Sichuan and
Hubei provinces.
</P>
<P>
Some 844,000 people are scheduled for resettlement, with
unforeseen factors most likely raising the figure to 1.2 million
people.
</P>
<P>
The Three Gorges Reservoir will inundated 31,000 hectares of
farmland, and will require the relocation of 1,599 industrial and
mining enterprises, as well as power transmission and
telecommunications facilities, harbors, small and medium-sized
hydro-electric power plants, roads and pumping stations.
</P>
<P>
The new reservoir, typical of facilities in gorges, will not
have a so-called "big-belly" section similar to other facilities
built on lakes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971104.0278 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> d p s 2191 China-Three Gorges-Backgrounder-12 Backgrounder: Three Gorges Guidelines to Resettlement (12) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANDOUPING (Three Gorges), November 4 (Xinhua) -- The key to
success of the Three Gorges Project rests with resettling more
than one million people living in areas scheduled for inundation.
Project developers have committed themselves to ensuring people
involved in the resettlement effort will have a better standard of
living.
</P>
<P>
The State Council's Resettlement Regulations on the Three
Gorges Project stipulate that "the state adheres to a guideline
of resettling people in the process of development. Relevant
local governments are responsible for resettlement, while the
allocation of resettlement funds and rational development of
resources give full play to the combined advantages of
agriculture, industry and commerce, with emphasis on the former.
Multiple channels will be used to resettle migrants in different
sectors and various means will be adopted to ensure their living
standards. Resettlement should create conditions enabling people
who have been resettled to develop local economies and have a
better life in the long-term."
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the number of people scheduled for
resettlement could surpass more than one million over a 17 year
period. The trans-century work is scheduled for completion in 2009
with an estimated static investment of 40 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The central government has granted a number of preferential
policies in this regard to ensure smooth operations, including the
establishment of an economic zone in the project area, and the
opening of Yichang, Wanxian and Fuling cities which have the
status of coastal open cities, as well as the integration of less
developed and developed regions across the country. The state is
committed to allocating some 500 million yuan annually to help
enterprises build new facilities and develop marketable products.
</P>
<P>
China has carried out trial resettlement programs since 1985,
with the latest effort commencing in 1993. Local governments have
allocated 8.58 billion yuan for the resettlement effort, with the
65,000 people resettled by October 1997, fulfilling proposed
targets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971104.0279 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-04 </DATE_TIME>
