<HEADLINE> Plane Crash in Guatemala, No one Injured </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO, November 3 (Xinhua) -- A plane crashed today in the
Villa Nueva municipality, south of Guatemala City, nobody was
injured in the accident.
</P>
<P>
A report from the capital of the Central American country said
two crew members, from the United States, came out without hurt in
the plane crash.
</P>
<P>
The report said the falldown of the Cessna plane just caused
material damages.
</P>
<P>
However, the plane ripped down power cables and caused minor
damages to some houses. Civil air navigation experts started an
investigation to the accident.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary reports said the plane ran out of fuel two miles
from the Guatemala Airport and a strong wind swept it to
the ground. 
</P>
