<HEADLINE> Rusedski Qualifies for ATP World Tour Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Second-seeded Greg Rusedski
of Britain beat wild card Nicklas Kulti of Sweden 7-6 (7-3), 6-4
in the opening round of the Stockholm Open ATP tournament Monday.
</P>
<P>
The victory enabled Rusedski to qualify for the eight-player
ATP Tour World Championships to be held at Hanover, Germany, next
week.
</P>
<P>
In the first set, Kulti saved two break points in the eighth
game and one set point in the 11th game. Rusedski then quickly
took charge by winning four straight points, making it 5-1 and won
the tiebreaker when Kulti double-faulted.
</P>
<P>
The second set was easier for Rusedski as he broke Kulti's
service for 3-2, then held on to win. 
</P>
