<HEADLINE> Pak Apex Court Issues Notices to PM, Law Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, November 3 (Xinhua) -- The Supreme Court of Pakistan
today ordered issuance of notices to the prime minister, the law
minister, the attorney-general, a few member of the National
Assembly, Pakistan TV and others to appear before the court, while
hearing a petition on a contempt case.
</P>
<P>
The petition was filed by Ikram Chaudhry, additional secretary
of the Supreme Court's Bar Association, in which he contended that
the respondents in the case are involved in contempt of the apex
court.
</P>
<P>
In this connection, he referred to the speeches delivered on
October 29 in the National Assembly and the Parliamentary Party's
meeting of the Pakistan Muslim League.
</P>
<P>
The court, headed by Chief Justice Sajjad Ali Shah, also
ordered the relevant departments to produce the record of the
speeches in the National Assembly and the Parliamentary Party
meeting, as well as the record of the press conference by Prime
Minister Nawaz Sharif held on the same day.
</P>
<P>
The court also ordered issuance of notice to Pakistan
Television (PTV) and its managing director. The court directed
that PTV should produce the audio/video record of the material and
the cartoon produced on anti-defection law.  
</P>
</TEXT>
