<HEADLINE> China Attaches Importance to Human Resources Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, November 3 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government
had accorded great importance to human resources development,
Chinese delegate Cui Ying stressed here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the Second Committee (Economic and Financial) of
the 52nd session of the General Assembly, Cui Ying said China
believed human resources development, centered around human
resources, was to train, develop and make full use of the capacity
of human resources to achieve sustained and sustainable social and
economic development.
</P>
<P>
Cui Ying said China's modernization relied on human resources
development, and China held that educated and qualified personnel
represented the most important resources for scientific and
technological progress as well as for economic and social
development.
</P>
<P>
Cui Ying said China had now made education a task of strategic
importance that commanded priority attention, and was making great
endeavors to develop education, enhance the scientific and
technological level by implementing preferential policies
encouraging and rewarding talented personnel.
</P>
<P>
Cui expressed the hope that the UN system and its agencies
would continue to pay priority attention to the human resources
development of developing countries with a view to promoting
international cooperation in this field. 
</P>
