<HEADLINE> Canada Destroys Landmine Stocks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Canadian Prime Minister Jean
Chretien destroyed the country's last operational stocks of
anti-personnel landmines here today.
</P>
<P>
The detonation fulfilled the government's pledge to do so
before the signing of the convention banning anti-personnel
landmines here next month.
</P>
<P>
"This is a great day for Canada. And an important step to the
Ottawa Conference in December," Chretien said.
</P>
<P>
Some 100 countries are expected to be here to sign the treaty
banning anti-personnel landmines, which was concluded in Oslo,
Norway, last month.
</P>
<P>
After today's detonation, Canada will retain a small number of
anti-personnel landmines to use for research in developing mine
detection and clearance equipment and to train military personnel
in de-mining techniques, the government said. 
