<HEADLINE> China Calls for Efforts to Advance Women's Status </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, November 3 (Xinhua) -- The international
community should continue to make efforts to advance the status of
women and create conditions for the promotion of women's
participation in development, Chinese delegate Cui Ying stressed
here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the Second Committee (Economic and Financial) of
the 52nd session of the General Assembly, Cui Ying said women were
an important force in human development, and without their active
and effective participation, economic and social development would
be difficult to achieve.
</P>
<P>
Cui Ying said it was only through their full participation that
women's political, economic and social advancement could be
secured.
</P>
<P>
Cui Ying said that since the convening of the Fourth World
Conference on Women, the international community had gained a
deeper insight into the role played by women in the resolution of
problems and difficulties facing women as well as in overcoming
obstacles to the advancement of women and their participation in
development.
</P>
<P>
However, the Chinese delegate said, there were regions in the
world which remained troubled with constant unrest; the economy of
a number of developing countries continued to deteriorate; and the
gap between the North and the South was widening. All this was
adversely affecting women's full participation in the development
process.
</P>
<P>
Cui said that the Chinese government had consistently advocated
equality between men and women by attaching importance to the
advancement of women and giving full play to women's initiatives,
creativity and potential in the political, economic and social
fields.
</P>
<P>
Cui expressed the hope that governments and the international
community would effectively honor their commitments by bolstering
women's full participation in the process of economic and social
development. She called on the UN system to play an active role in
this regard. 
</P>
</TEXT>
