<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Germany today sharply criticized
Iraq for its refusal to let a United Nations arms inspection team
enter a military installation, describing Iraq's policies as
"cynical".
</P>
<P>
"I condemn in the strongest terms the renewed refusal of Iraq
to cooperate without conditions with the U.N. disarmament
mission...," said German Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel in a
statement.
