<HEADLINE> Russian Rocket Troops Rebuilt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Integration of the strategic
rocket troops, the military space forces and the space defense
forces into a single new division of the Russian armed forces has
been completed, the Interfax news agency reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to the troops' press center, commander of the
new-look strategic rocket troops Vladimir Yakovlev has submitted a
corresponding report to Defense Minister Igor Sergeyev.
</P>
<P>
The integration process began in July 28, 1997, and ended in
November 1, the report said. During this period, the strategic
rocket troops took over the military command agencies, military
units, educational establishments and enterprises of the military
space forces and the space defense forces.
</P>
<P>
Yakovlev said the troops are currently controlled by the
central command of the strategic rocket troops. The general
principles for maintaining the troops' combat readiness, their
training and command within the unified structure have been
determined, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
