<DOCNO> XIE19971104.0326 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IFC Finances Small-Scale Infrastructure in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 3 (Xinhua) -- The International Finance
Corporation (IFC) today announced the signing of an agreement with
Nocco Uco Financial Services Lt. (NUFSL) to provide a loan of 10
million U.S. dollars to help small-scale infrastructure in India.
</P>
<P>
The IFC financing, of which 5 million dollars will be
syndicated, will help the company expand its operations into
small-scale infrastructure projects in power, transport, and
telecommunications, as well as in commercially operated municipal
infrastructure facilities.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the NUFSL will continue to focus on its
traditional small and medium enterprise clients.
</P>
<P>
NUFSL is a medium-sized diversified financial services company
based in India which is involved in leasing, hire purchase,
merchant banking, working capital, and trade finance.
</P>
<P>
IFC is a member of the World Bank Group and also the largest
multilateral source of equity and loan financing for private
sector projects in developing countries. Up to date, IFC has
approved investments of more than 2.5 billion dollars in 155
companies in India, including nearly 500 million dollars in the
financial sector and over 945 million dollars in infrastructure
projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
